content:
Ah, got it—thanks for clarifying.

Since Git says:

```
nothing to commit, working tree clean
```

That means your commit was successfully recorded locally, and you just need to push to GitHub now:

Run:

```bash
git push origin main --force
```

Because you've rewritten history (with `git filter-repo`), a force push is necessary and safe at this point since you've removed the secrets already.

This command will sync your cleaned-up commit history with GitHub, resolving your secret detection issue once and for all.
